credit_line: Williams College Museum of Art, Prendergast Archive and Study Center, Gift of Mrs. Charles Prendergast
title: Guide Michelin, France
inscriptions: With pencil notations by Charles Prendergast and various ephemera from the trip. Upside down pencil inscription on first page "31-6u9 7178-mlo". Pg. 22 writing "1645 Coitir, Splose 66, 0.1 47". Pg. 162 finger print mark. pg. 202 mark next to "Canadel (Le)". pg. 337 and 202 dried pressed flowers. Pg. 988 pencil notes of places and distances in Km. A.1.153.A-J ephemera found in book.
